there can be 4 competencies

01:15:42.000 --> 01:15:45.000
if we only define the corporate or management.

01:15:45.000 --> 01:15:48.000
Then it should be brought to the employees

01:15:48.000 --> 01:15:51.000
in the right way.

01:15:51.000 --> 01:15:54.000
Maybe the model is poorly adapted for business tasks

01:15:54.000 --> 01:15:57.000
and it does not meet the goals of the company?

01:15:57.000 --> 01:16:00.000
Maybe it is borrowed from another company?

01:16:00.000 --> 01:16:03.000
Or maybe the competence is wrong?

01:16:09.000 --> 01:16:12.000
When we talked about the behavior standards

01:16:12.000 --> 01:16:15.000
that we describe,

01:16:15.000 --> 01:16:18.000
we talked about the high efficiency of the employees.

01:16:18.000 --> 01:16:21.000
The next one.

01:16:21.000 --> 01:16:24.000
There could be mistakes during the implementation.

01:16:24.000 --> 01:16:27.000
The most common mistake is

01:16:27.000 --> 01:16:30.000
that the employees do not understand

01:16:30.000 --> 01:16:33.000
the purpose of the competencies.

01:16:33.000 --> 01:16:36.000
But there are some.

01:16:36.000 --> 01:16:39.000
The staff evaluated it,

01:16:39.000 --> 01:16:42.000
but it is not always the case.

01:16:42.000 --> 01:16:45.000
Maybe the management does not consider

01:16:45.000 --> 01:16:48.000
them important.

01:16:48.000 --> 01:16:51.000
It means that there was no proper attention

01:16:51.000 --> 01:16:54.000
to involve the managers in the process.

01:16:54.000 --> 01:16:57.000
It is important that the managers feel like their own.

01:16:57.000 --> 01:17:00.000
If they cannot participate in all stages,

01:17:00.000 --> 01:17:03.000
it is important to gather the managers,

01:17:03.000 --> 01:17:06.000
to introduce them,

01:17:06.000 --> 01:17:09.000
to answer their questions,

01:17:09.000 --> 01:17:12.000
to listen to their comments.

01:17:12.000 --> 01:17:15.000
To make changes, to talk again.

01:17:15.000 --> 01:17:18.000
So that the managers understand

01:17:18.000 --> 01:17:21.000
that they are also involved.

01:17:21.000 --> 01:17:24.000
The size of the participation will remain behind the scenes.

01:17:24.000 --> 01:17:27.000
Maybe the competencies are not integrated

01:17:27.000 --> 01:17:30.000
into other management systems.

01:17:30.000 --> 01:17:33.000
What does it mean?

01:17:33.000 --> 01:17:36.000
We developed the competencies,

01:17:36.000 --> 01:17:39.000
we evaluate them,

01:17:39.000 --> 01:17:42.000
but it is not easy to develop the profiles,

01:17:42.000 --> 01:17:45.000
develop the questions,

01:17:45.000 --> 01:17:48.000
develop the exercises and use them during selection.

01:17:48.000 --> 01:17:51.000
Maybe we did not have time,

01:17:51.000 --> 01:17:54.000
or we did not consider them important,

01:17:54.000 --> 01:17:57.000
or we did not train the people who do the selection.

01:17:57.000 --> 01:18:00.000
There are many reasons.

01:18:00.000 --> 01:18:03.000
Once again, both at the development stage and at the implementation stage.

01:18:03.000 --> 01:18:06.000
The next reason why the model of competencies

01:18:06.000 --> 01:18:09.000
is important is that its development

01:18:09.000 --> 01:18:12.000
took place during a difficult time for the company.

01:18:12.000 --> 01:18:15.000
What do we mean by a difficult time?

01:18:15.000 --> 01:18:18.000
It can be restructuring,

01:18:18.000 --> 01:18:21.000
it can be a period when the company experienced financial difficulties.

01:18:21.000 --> 01:18:24.000
There may be another aspect,

01:18:24.000 --> 01:18:27.000
there are no financial difficulties,

01:18:27.000 --> 01:18:30.000
but there are many significant changes in the company.

01:18:30.000 --> 01:18:33.000
Maybe the shareholder composition changes,

01:18:33.000 --> 01:18:36.000
or some other projects are happening.

01:18:36.000 --> 01:18:39.000
This project is lost

01:18:39.000 --> 01:18:42.000
and it does not get the attention it deserves.

01:18:42.000 --> 01:18:47.000
What are the reasons for the failure of the competencies?

01:18:47.000 --> 01:18:50.000
The next reason why competencies may not work

01:18:50.000 --> 01:18:53.000
is that they are misused.

01:18:53.000 --> 01:18:58.000
What are the reasons for the failure of the competencies?

01:18:58.000 --> 01:19:01.000
We are talking about the cases

01:19:01.000 --> 01:19:04.000
when competencies are used as a strict list

01:19:04.000 --> 01:19:07.000
according to which a person is evaluated.

01:19:07.000 --> 01:19:10.000
There is no flexibility in their application, which is unacceptable.

01:19:10.000 --> 01:19:13.000
There are also cases when the behavior indicators

01:19:13.000 --> 01:19:16.000
of certain companies are replaced

01:19:16.000 --> 01:19:19.000
by the personal interpretation of the supervisor of the evaluated employees.

01:19:19.000 --> 01:19:22.000
When he puts into the competencies the meaning

01:19:22.000 --> 01:19:25.000
that is understandable to him, that is close to him,

01:19:25.000 --> 01:19:28.000
it is not always the meaning that corresponds to the definition

01:19:28.000 --> 01:19:31.000
that was proposed by the group of developers.

01:19:31.000 --> 01:19:34.000
Therefore, it is also important to monitor this point

01:19:34.000 --> 01:19:37.000
and to control, to keep an eye on the pulse,

01:19:37.000 --> 01:19:40.000
to train supervisors,

01:19:40.000 --> 01:19:43.000
to talk to them,

01:19:43.000 --> 01:19:46.000
to help them in the application of this model.

01:19:46.000 --> 01:19:49.000
What else should we pay attention to when working with competencies?

01:19:49.000 --> 01:19:52.000
First, competencies can intersect.

01:19:52.000 --> 01:19:55.000
To check whether competencies intersect,

01:19:55.000 --> 01:19:58.000
it is necessary to determine for yourself,

01:19:58.000 --> 01:20:01.000
to assume,

01:20:01.000 --> 01:20:04.000
whether two employees can work in a company,

01:20:04.000 --> 01:20:07.000
one of which has one of the competencies

01:20:07.000 --> 01:20:10.000
at a high level of development,

01:20:10.000 --> 01:20:13.000
and the other is absent, and vice versa.

01:20:13.000 --> 01:20:16.000
If we can answer the question,

01:20:16.000 --> 01:20:19.000
yes, this is possible, then competencies do not intersect.

01:20:19.000 --> 01:20:22.000
If we can answer the question, yes, this is possible, then competencies do not intersect.

01:20:22.000 --> 01:20:25.000
Then there are two ways.

01:20:25.000 --> 01:20:28.000
Either we give up one of the competencies,

01:20:28.000 --> 01:20:31.000
or we somehow include one in the other.

01:20:31.000 --> 01:20:34.000
Next, competencies can be very confusing.

01:20:34.000 --> 01:20:37.000
When we try to determine

01:20:37.000 --> 01:20:40.000
the maximum number of behavioral indicators for them,

01:20:40.000 --> 01:20:43.000
and thus the competency becomes

01:20:43.000 --> 01:20:46.000
simply incomprehensible to the perception.

01:20:46.000 --> 01:20:49.000
Next, it is contradictory competencies.

01:20:49.000 --> 01:20:52.000
When competencies contain statements

01:20:52.000 --> 01:20:55.000
that contradict each other.

01:20:55.000 --> 01:20:58.000
For example, describing the leaders and how the leader makes decisions,

01:20:58.000 --> 01:21:01.000
there may be a behavioral indicator,

01:21:01.000 --> 01:21:04.000
for example, such that the leader

01:21:04.000 --> 01:21:07.000
makes decisions himself and takes responsibility.

01:21:07.000 --> 01:21:10.000
And then there is a little bit less talk about

01:21:10.000 --> 01:21:13.000
that when making a decision, he consults with colleagues

01:21:13.000 --> 01:21:16.000
or, for example, with subordinates.

01:21:16.000 --> 01:21:19.000
It is clear that these are things that are a little contradictory,

01:21:19.000 --> 01:21:22.000
and therefore competencies need to be calculated and analyzed

01:21:22.000 --> 01:21:25.000
so that this does not happen, then it will be difficult to apply them.

01:21:25.000 --> 01:21:28.000
The next point is when competencies

01:21:28.000 --> 01:21:31.000
incorrectly define standards.

01:21:31.000 --> 01:21:34.000
And the mistake is that competencies are not divided by levels.

01:21:34.000 --> 01:21:37.000
And thus, qualified and unqualified performers,

01:21:37.000 --> 01:21:40.000
that is, people who have and do not have competencies,

01:21:40.000 --> 01:21:43.000
they receive the same rating.

01:21:43.000 --> 01:21:46.000
This is, again, a question of formulation.

01:21:46.000 --> 01:21:49.000
Therefore, at the stage of formulating the list,

01:21:49.000 --> 01:21:52.000
these questions should be asked.

01:21:52.000 --> 01:21:55.000
The next point is when competencies in their definition

01:21:55.000 --> 01:21:58.000
as indicators contain not actions, but results.

01:21:58.000 --> 01:22:01.000
Colleagues, once again, competencies are those characteristics of a person

01:22:01.000 --> 01:22:04.000
that we in the company can measure at the behavioral level.

01:22:04.000 --> 01:22:07.000
Thus, in determining competencies,

01:22:08.000 --> 01:22:11.000
we should always answer the question of what a person does,

01:22:11.000 --> 01:22:14.000
but in no case should we describe some goals and results

01:22:14.000 --> 01:22:17.000
that a person with this competence should achieve.

01:22:17.000 --> 01:22:20.000
We can say that the model of competence is successfully implemented.

01:22:20.000 --> 01:22:23.000
When can we say that the model of competence is successfully implemented?

01:22:23.000 --> 01:22:26.000
First of all, it is necessary to understand

01:22:26.000 --> 01:22:29.000
that the model of competence is not a model of competence.

01:22:29.000 --> 01:22:32.000
It is a model of competence that is implemented

01:22:32.000 --> 01:22:35.000
in a way that is not a model of competence.

01:22:36.000 --> 01:22:39.000
First of all, it is implemented when it is constantly being improved.

01:22:39.000 --> 01:22:42.000
When employees discuss competencies that are necessary for their work.

01:22:42.000 --> 01:22:45.000
That is, competencies themselves are part of professional slang.

01:22:45.000 --> 01:22:48.000
And employees operate them.

01:22:48.000 --> 01:22:51.000
If you hear when one employee says to another,

01:22:51.000 --> 01:22:54.000
but now you have not shown competence in your team,

01:22:54.000 --> 01:22:57.000
it means that competencies have entered your corporate slang.

01:22:57.000 --> 01:23:00.000
It has become the language you started to speak.

01:23:00.000 --> 01:23:03.000
This is one of the reasons why you are not able to work in a team.

01:23:04.000 --> 01:23:07.000
And, of course, we can talk about success when our managers

01:23:07.000 --> 01:23:10.000
or sub-units of the middle-high-ranking branch

01:23:10.000 --> 01:23:13.000
perceive competence as a tool of staff management

01:23:13.000 --> 01:23:16.000
that helps them in their daily work.

01:23:16.000 --> 01:23:19.000
To summarize, we will formulate several recommendations

01:23:19.000 --> 01:23:22.000
about what is needed for competence to work.

01:23:22.000 --> 01:23:25.000
Colleagues, first of all, an objective reason for the creation

01:23:25.000 --> 01:23:28.000
and implementation of the competence model is needed.

01:23:28.000 --> 01:23:31.000
It is necessary to understand that the competence model

01:23:32.000 --> 01:23:35.000
is a very important reason for the creation and implementation of the competence model.

01:23:35.000 --> 01:23:38.000
Second, it is necessary to involve line managers and employees

01:23:38.000 --> 01:23:41.000
at all stages of work.

01:23:41.000 --> 01:23:44.000
It is necessary to organize a competent internal PR project.

01:23:44.000 --> 01:23:47.000
That is, to inform about how and why it happens,

01:23:47.000 --> 01:23:50.000
what benefit the company, the line manager,

01:23:50.000 --> 01:23:53.000
and the employees get.

01:23:53.000 --> 01:23:56.000
It is necessary to teach how to use competencies

01:23:56.000 --> 01:23:59.000
when they are developed.

01:24:00.000 --> 01:24:03.000
It is necessary to repeat the general practice of using competencies.

01:24:03.000 --> 01:24:06.000
That is, when evaluating the developed competence for the first time,

01:24:06.000 --> 01:24:09.000
it is necessary to be flexible and test again

01:24:09.000 --> 01:24:12.000
whether the competencies you have formulated

01:24:12.000 --> 01:24:15.000
are really the standards,

01:24:15.000 --> 01:24:18.000
the priority standards of behavior

01:24:18.000 --> 01:24:21.000
that are necessary for your company.

01:24:21.000 --> 01:24:24.000
And the last one is a mandatory,

01:24:24.000 --> 01:24:27.000
let's say, gradual integration of competence

01:24:28.000 --> 01:24:31.000
into all policies and procedures of the staff management service.

01:24:31.000 --> 01:24:34.000
Colleagues, I wish you success and patience

01:24:34.000 --> 01:24:37.000
in implementing this project in your companies

